content.p:
“parcel” means a postal item, containing goods with
									or without commercial value, with a weight not exceeding 31,5
									kg excluding items of correspondence;

"parcel
									delivery services" means services involving the clearance,
									sorting, transport and distribution of parcels;

"subcontractor" means an undertaking that
									provides the clearance, sorting, transport or distribution of
									parcels for the parcel delivery service provider;

the definitions of “consumer”, "trader"
									and “sales contract” in paragraphs 1, 2 and 5 of Article 2 of
									Directive 2011/83/EU;

the domestic and any other relevant tariffs of the
									comparable parcel delivery services in the originating Member
									State and in the destination Member State;

bilateral volumes, specific transportation or
									handling costs, other relevant costs and service quality
									standards;
